Spanish: Caza de Zenmas

English: Almani asked for help with reducing the Zenma population as they're causing problems with forestation in Gouthan Mountains. Could you kill 15 of them?
Spanish: Almani ha pedido ayuda para reducir la población de Zenmas, ya que están causando problemas con la forestación en las Montañas Gouthan. ¿Podrías eliminar a 15 de ellos?

English: You can find Zenma flying above Gouthan Mountains.
Spanish: Puedes encontrar a los Zenmas volando sobre las Montañas Gouthan.

English: Hey look, a flying rat!
Spanish: ¡Oye, mira, una rata voladora!

English: Almani asked for Longwings to be exterminated, as they have been attacking civilians. Could you kill 15 of them?
Spanish: Almani ha pedido que se extermine a los Longwings, ya que han estado atacando a civiles. ¿Podrías deshacerte de 15 de ellos?

English: You can find Longwings flying South-East of the Clockworks Cage in the mountains.
Spanish: Puedes encontrar a los Longwings volando al Sureste de la Jaula de Clockworks en las montañas.

English: Baby Meteonyker
Spanish: Meteonyker Bebé

English: Almani asked for Fafnirs to be exterminated, before they grow into Dragons! Please could you kill 15 of them?
Spanish: ¡Almani ha pedido que se extermine a los Fafnirs, antes de que se conviertan en Dragones! Por favor, ¿podrías deshacerte de 15 de ellos?

English: You can find Fafnirs flying near the Volcano in Darkon 3, Brekin.
Spanish: Puedes encontrar a los Fafnirs volando cerca del Volcán en Darkon 3, Brekin.

English: Prehistoric Birds
Spanish: Pájaros Prehistóricos

English: Almani asked for Gorrudas to be exterminated. They are an imminent threat! Please could you kill 15 of them?
Spanish: Almani ha pedido que se extermine a los Gorrudas. ¡Son una amenaza inminente! Por favor, ¿podrías deshacerte de 15 de ellos?

English: You can find Gorrudas flying West of the Deadwallderness, over the mountains.
Spanish: Puedes encontrar a los Gorrudas volando al Oeste del Desierto Muerto, sobre las montañas.

English: Flying Circus (2)
Spanish: Circo Volador (2)

Spanish: Dior asked for further help regarding the Rockepeller threat. Could you get rid of the Lord Rockepeller?

English: You can find the Lord Rockepeller flying between Flaris and Darkon continents.
Spanish: You can find the Lord Rockepeller flying between Flaris and Darkon continents.

Spanish: Almani asked for further help regarding the Longwings threat. Could you get rid of the Lord Longwing?

Spanish: Almani asked for further help regarding the Gorruda threat. Could you get rid of the Lord Gorruda?

English: You can find the $QUEST_END_KILL_NAME$ flying West of the Deadwallderness, over the mountains.
Spanish: Puedes encontrar al $QUEST_END_KILL_NAME$ volando al oeste de Deadwallderness, sobre las montañas.

Spanish: Caza de Zenmas (2)

English: Almani asked for further help regarding the Zenma threat. Could you get rid of the Lord Zenma?
Spanish: Almani asked for further help regarding the Zenma threat. Could you get rid of the Lord Zenma?

Spanish: You can find the Lord Zenma flying above Gouthan Mountains.

English: You can get $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from any type of Chimeradon.
Spanish: Puedes conseguir $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$s de cualquier tipo de Chimeradon.

English: You can get $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from any type of Bearnerky.
Spanish: Puedes obtener $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$s de cualquier tipo de Bearnerky.

English: You can get $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from any type of Muffrin.
Spanish: Puedes obtener $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ de cualquier tipo de Muffrin.

English: You can get $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from any type of Popcrank.
Spanish: Puedes obtener $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$s de cualquier tipo de Popcrank.

English: You can collect $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from all types of Red Mantis.
Spanish: Puedes conseguir $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$s de todos los tipos de Red Mantis.

English: Obsessed with Crystals! (1)
Spanish: ¡Obsesionado con los Cristales! (1)

English: Obsessed with Crystals! (2)
Spanish: ¡Obsesionado con los Cristales! (2)

English: Obsessed with Crystals! (3)
Spanish: ¡Obsesionado con los Cristales! (3)

English: Obsessed with Crystals! (4)
Spanish: ¡Obsesionado con los Cristales! (4)

English: Obsessed with Crystals! (5)
Spanish: ¡Obsesionado con los Cristales! (5)

English: Crystals! Hmmm.... $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$s! Could you please bring me some $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$!?
Spanish: ¡¡Cristales!! Mmmm... ¡$QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$s! ¿Podrías traerme algo de $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$?

English: You can get $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from any type of Medumet.
Spanish: Puedes obtener $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ de cualquier tipo de Medumet.

English: You can get $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from any type of Yetti.
Spanish: Puedes obtener $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ de cualquier tipo de Yetti.

English: You can get $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from any type of Augu.
Spanish: Puedes obtener $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ de cualquier tipo de Augu.

English: You can get $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from any type of Ghost of the Forgotten.
Spanish: Puedes obtener $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ de cualquier tipo de Fantasma de los Olvidados.

English: You can get $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from any type of Mammoth.
Spanish: Puedes obtener $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ de cualquier tipo de Mammoth.

English: You did it! Hooray! Here's your reward. Come back soon!
Spanish: ¡Lo hiciste! ¡Hurra! Aquí está tu recompensa. ¡Vuelve pronto!

English: More! More!
Spanish: ¡Más! ¡Más!

English: Bring Broken Wings
Spanish: Trae Alas Rotas

English: Tigar Bites
Spanish: Mordeduras Tigar

English: Googly-Eyed Gogloo
Spanish: Gogloo Ojos Saltones

English: Nippy Waters
Spanish: Agua Refrescante

English: Hard Shell of the Creper
Spanish: Choncha Dura Creper

English: Crumbly Purple Essence
Spanish: Esencia Púrpura Desmenuzable

English: A Gray Picture of Dorian
Spanish: Una imagen gris de Dorian

English: King of Coral Island
Spanish: Rey de Isla Coral

English: Letter in a Bottle
Spanish: Carta en una botella

English: Hello adventurer... would you bring me $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the Atrox? I want to build giant wings I can soar the skies with! Bring me all you can find...
Spanish: Hola aventurero... ¿Me traerías $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ del Atrox? ¡Quiero construir alas gigantes con las que pueda volar por los cielos! Tráeme todo lo que puedas encontrar..

English: Tigars are known to have some of the strongest teeth in all of Madrigal. If you come across $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ could you bring me a few? I'm crafting a giant dagger... it'll be HUGE!
Spanish: Se sabe que los Tigars tienen los dientes más fuertes de todo Madrigal. Si encuentras $QUEST_END ITEM_NAME$, ¿podrías traerme algunos? Estoy creando una daga gigante... ¡¡será ENORME!!

English: The glass inside a Meral's $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ can enhance a person's vision thrice their normal spotting distance. Collect me enough and I could build a telescope to peer halfway across the globe!
Spanish: El cristal dentro del $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ de un Meral puede mejorar la visión hasta tres veces su distancia normal. ¡¡Reúnanme lo suficiente y podría construir un telescopio para mirar al otro lado del mundo!!

English: All this inventing has me famished! Could you go get me some of the Kingster's $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$? We'll eat like kings! Don't worry, I'll share...
Spanish: ¡¡Todo este inventar me tiene hambrienta!! ¿Podrías traerme un poco de $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ de Kingster? ¡Comeremos como reyes! No te preocupes, lo compartiré.

English: After all that seafood I couldn't eat another bite! For this next invention, I need $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the large crabs called Creper. From their hard carapace I will craft the strongest of armors. I forsee a fate in which doning this armor will save Coral Island!
Spanish: ¡Después de todo ese marisco no pude comer más! Para este próximo invento, necesito $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ de los cangrejos grandes llamados Creper. Con su duro caparazón crearé las armaduras más fuertes. ¡Preveo que usar esta armadura salvará Isla Coral!

English: The Naga are powerful warriors of the sea... their $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ are said to hold magical powers that can be used to harness purple energy. I have a healthy fear of Purple Magic, but what doesn't kill you only makes you stronger.
Spanish: Los Naga son poderosos guerreros del mar. Se dice que sus $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ tienen poderes mágicos que aprovechan la energía púrpura. Tengo miedo a la Magia Púrpura, pero lo que no te mata te hace más fuerte.

English: The Dorian have risen from the seas around our island! Please defeat them and collect their $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ as proof. My inventions can only hold them back for so long...
Spanish: ¡Los Dorian han surgido de los mares que rodean nuestra isla! Por favor, derrótalos y recoge su $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$. Mis inventos sólo pueden detenerlos por un tiempo.

English: The $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ of the Okean must be mine! I know having their crown won't make me a king, but it will put me on the path of my dream. To be King of Coral Island!
Spanish: ¡El $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ del Okean debe ser mío! Sé que tener su corona no me convertirá en rey, pero me pondrá en el camino de mi sueño. ¡Ser Rey de Isla Coral!

English: With the $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the Kraken, I could finally write to all my friends across the oceans. There's never enough time to keep up with everyone...
Spanish: Con el $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ del Kraken, finalmente pude escribirle a todos mis amigos al otro lado del océano. Nunca hay tiempo suficiente para seguir a todos.

English: You may find $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from any of the Atrox crawling around the island.
Spanish: Puedes encontrar $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ de cualquiera de los Atrox que se arrastran por la isla.

English: You may find $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from Tigars around the island.
Spanish: Puedes encontrar $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ de Tigars en toda la isla.

English: You may find $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the Meral patroling the beaches.
Spanish: Puedes encontrar $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ del Meral patrullando las playas.

English: You may find delicious $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from Kingsters in shallow waters around the island.
Spanish: Puedes encontrar deliciosos $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ de Kingsters en aguas someras alrededor de la isla.

English: You may find tough $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from Creper around the beach area.
Spanish: Posiblemente encuentres $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ difíciles de Creper en el área de la playa.

English: You may find $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from Naga around Coral Island.
Spanish: Puedes encontrar $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ de Naga alrededor de Isla Coral.

English: You may find $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ left behind by Dorian around Coral Island.
Spanish: Posiblemente encuentres $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ de Dorian alrededor de Isla Coral.

English: You may find magnificient $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from Okean, deep in the waters of Coral Island's seas.
Spanish: Puedes encontrar $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ magníficos de Okean, en lo profundo del mar de Isla Coral.

English: You may find $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ inside the bellies of the deep-sea Kraken.
Spanish: Es posible que encuentres $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ en el vientre del Kraken de aguas profundas.

English: Please, don't make me go collect $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ all on my own... I'm too busy dreaming up new inventions!
Spanish: Por favor, no me obligues a recolectar $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ solo. ¡Estoy demasiado ocupado con nuevos inventos!

English: Thank you for collecting all those $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$, adventurer! Soon I'll be soaring the skies with ease. See you at the Rainbow Race!
Spanish: ¡Gracias por reunir todos esos $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$, aventurero! Pronto estaré surcando los cielos. ¡Nos vemos en la Carrera Arcoíris!

English: Thank you for collecting all those $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$, adventurer! Soon I'll have the biggest dagger in Madrigal. Hehehe, catch me showing off to the Demians!
Spanish: ¡Gracias por reunir todos esos $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$, aventurero! Pronto tendré el puñal más grande de Madrigal. Jejeje, ¡Presumiré ante todos!

English: Thank you for collecting all those $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$, adventurer! Soon I'll be able to see the sights without ever leaving my home!
Spanish: ¡Gracias por reunir todos esos $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$, aventurero! ¡Pronto podré ver los lugares de interés sin tener que salir de casa!

English: Thank you for collecting all those $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$, adventurer! We're going to be so full! Eat up, it's time to feast!
Spanish: ¡Gracias por reunir todos esos $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$, aventurero! ¡Vamos a estar muy llenos! ¡Come, es hora de un festín!

English: Thank you for collecting all those $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$, adventurer! Soon I'll have armor enough to defend Coral Island against all evil!
Spanish: ¡Gracias por reunir todos esos $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$, aventurero! ¡Pronto tendré suficiente armadura para defender Isla Coral contra todo mal!

English: Thank you for collecting all those $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$, adventurer! Soon I'll know more about this Purple Magic... Perhaps one day enough to stop its evil from taking over Coral Island.
Spanish: ¡Gracias por reunir todos esos $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$, aventurero! Pronto sabré más sobre esta Magia Púrpura. Quizás algún día sea suficiente para evitar que su maldad se apodere de Isla Coral.

English: Thank you for collecting all those $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$, adventurer! Those fishy creatures have a strange power that makes them age slower than others. Perhaps studying their teeth can give us insight to the Dorian's special powers.
Spanish: ¡Gracias por reunir todos esos $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$, aventurero! Esas criaturas parecidas a peces tienen un extraño poder que les hace envejecer más lentamente. Quizás estudiar sus dientes pueda darnos una idea de los poderes especiales de Dorian.

English: Thank you for collecting all those $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$, adventurer! It's just a dream... but I hope to one day greet you again as King of Coral Island.
Spanish: ¡Gracias por reunir todos esos $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$, aventurero! Es solo un sueño... pero espero saludarte algún día como Rey de Isla Coral.

English: Thank you for collecting all those $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$, adventurer! I've decided to write these letters and deliver them myself. Thank you for everything... I hope to see you again one day!
Spanish: ¡Gracias por reunir todos esos $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$, aventurero! He decidido escribir estas cartas y entregarlas yo mismo. Gracias por todo. ¡Espero volver a verte algún día!

English: That isn't nearly enough $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ for me to build one of my grand inventions... come back with more!
Spanish: No es suficiente $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ para construir mi gran invento... ¡Tráeme más!

English: $QUEST_END_NPC_NAME$ cackles with glee! Soon their inventions will become a reality.
Spanish: ¡$QUEST_END_NPC_NAME$ se ríe de alegría! Pronto sus inventos se harán realidad.

English: The Skulls of the Hundur Sharpfoot
Spanish: The Skulls of the Hundur Sharpfoot

English: The Hundur Sharpfoot gather near Kaillun’s borders, and their skulls bear strange markings. The Muran need them to decipher the secrets behind their rituals.
Spanish: The Hundur Sharpfoot gather near Kaillun’s borders, and their skulls bear strange markings. The Muran need them to decipher the secrets behind their rituals.

English: Excellent! The Muran are counting on you. Go gather 325 $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ and return once you have enough. You can find them on the Hundur Sharpfoot.
Spanish: Excellent! The Muran are counting on you. Go gather 325 $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ and return once you have enough. You can find them on the Hundur Sharpfoot.

English: I see… but these creatures are growing more aggressive. Come back if you change your mind.
Spanish: I see… but these creatures are growing more aggressive. Come back if you change your mind.

English: You haven't gathered enough skulls yet… Keep going, each specimen is important to us.
Spanish: You haven't gathered enough skulls yet… Keep going, each specimen is important to us.

English: Perfect! These skulls will be of great use to us. Kaillun thanks you for your determination.
Spanish: Perfect! These skulls will be of great use to us. Kaillun thanks you for your determination.

English: The Skulls of the Samoset
Spanish: The Skulls of the Samoset

English: The Samoset spirits have grown increasingly aggressive in the plains. The sages of Kaillun seek their skulls to understand the source of their unusual unrest.
Spanish: The Samoset spirits have grown increasingly aggressive in the plains. The sages of Kaillun seek their skulls to understand the source of their unusual unrest.

English: Thank you! The Samoset spirits are becoming unstable. Bring back 325 $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the Samoset so we can analyze their unrest.
Spanish: Thank you! The Samoset spirits are becoming unstable. Bring back 325 $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the Samoset so we can analyze their unrest.

English: Very well… but their unrest intensifies each day. Return if you change your mind.
Spanish: Very well… but their unrest intensifies each day. Return if you change your mind.

English: You still don't have enough… Keep going, we must understand what's disturbing them.
Spanish: You still don't have enough… Keep going, we must understand what's disturbing them.

English: Perfect! These skulls will help us uncover the truth. Thank you for your help.
Spanish: Perfect! These skulls will help us uncover the truth. Thank you for your help.

English: The Claws of the Kyouchish
Spanish: The Claws of the Kyouchish

English: The Kyouchish have been injuring many Muran scouts with their corrosive strikes. Their claws are needed to craft a protective remedy.
Spanish: The Kyouchish have been injuring many Muran scouts with their corrosive strikes. Their claws are needed to craft a protective remedy.

English: Good! Their claws are poisoning our scouts. Bring back 325 $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the Kyouchish.
Spanish: Good! Their claws are poisoning our scouts. Bring back 325 $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the Kyouchish.

English: I understand… but we're running out of remedies. Return if you wish to help.
Spanish: I understand… but we're running out of remedies. Return if you wish to help.

English: You're still missing some. The Kyouchish are dangerous, stay careful.
Spanish: You're still missing some. The Kyouchish are dangerous, stay careful.

English: Excellent! With these claws, our healers can prepare a proper antidote.
Spanish: Excellent! With these claws, our healers can prepare a proper antidote.

English: The Kanonicus Antidote
Spanish: The Kanonicus Antidote

English: The Kanonicus carry a natural antidote within their dorsal glands. Kaillun urgently needs it to heal warriors poisoned by the Lycans.
Spanish: The Kanonicus carry a natural antidote within their dorsal glands. Kaillun urgently needs it to heal warriors poisoned by the Lycans.

English: Thank you! Their natural antidote is vital for our wounded soldiers. Bring back 325 $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the Kanonicus.
Spanish: Thank you! Their natural antidote is vital for our wounded soldiers. Bring back 325 $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the Kanonicus.

English: A shame… several warriors are still waiting to be treated.
Spanish: A shame… several warriors are still waiting to be treated.

English: You don’t have enough yet. Hurry, every drop counts.
Spanish: You don’t have enough yet. Hurry, every drop counts.

English: Perfect! Thanks to you, we can finally treat our wounded.
Spanish: Perfect! Thanks to you, we can finally treat our wounded.

English: The Magic Skulls of the Redcloud
Spanish: The Magic Skulls of the Redcloud

English: The Redcloud generate a mysterious energy within their skulls. Muran shamans want to study this magic to reinforce the city's protective wards.
Spanish: The Redcloud generate a mysterious energy within their skulls. Muran shamans want to study this magic to reinforce the city's protective wards.

English: Very well! Their skulls contain a mysterious energy. We must study it. Bring back 325 $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the Redcloud.
Spanish: Very well! Their skulls contain a mysterious energy. We must study it. Bring back 325 $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the Redcloud.

English: Alright… but this magic could strengthen our defenses.
Spanish: Alright… but this magic could strengthen our defenses.

English: You don’t have enough energy-charged skulls yet. Keep going!
Spanish: You don’t have enough energy-charged skulls yet. Keep going!

English: Excellent work! These skulls are a true source of power.
Spanish: Excellent work! These skulls are a true source of power.

English: The Devil’s Teeth
Spanish: The Devil’s Teeth

English: A strange corruption spreads through Kaillun as Devil Spirits multiply. Their teeth contain a demonic essence the sages wish to seal away.
Spanish: A strange corruption spreads through Kaillun as Devil Spirits multiply. Their teeth contain a demonic essence the sages wish to seal away.

English: Be brave! The Devil Spirits are growing in number. Their teeth must be sealed. Bring back 325 $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the Devil Spirits.
Spanish: Be brave! The Devil Spirits are growing in number. Their teeth must be sealed. Bring back 325 $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the Devil Spirits.

English: I understand… but their influence spreads further each night. Return carefully.
Spanish: I understand… but their influence spreads further each night. Return carefully.

English: Not enough teeth to contain the demonic energy yet. Keep gathering.
Spanish: Not enough teeth to contain the demonic energy yet. Keep gathering.

English: Very good! These teeth will be purified and neutralized. You’ve done us a great service.
Spanish: Very good! These teeth will be purified and neutralized. You’ve done us a great service.

English: The Bloodstained Fangs of the Hellhound
Spanish: The Bloodstained Fangs of the Hellhound

English: Hellhounds roam dangerously close to Kaillun, and their bloodied fangs leave lingering wounds. The Muran need them to forge weapons capable of driving these beasts back.
Spanish: Hellhounds roam dangerously close to Kaillun, and their bloodied fangs leave lingering wounds. The Muran need them to forge weapons capable of driving these beasts back.

English: Perfect! Their blood-soaked fangs are deadly. Bring back 325 $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the Hellhounds to us for forging.
Spanish: Perfect! Their blood-soaked fangs are deadly. Bring back 325 $QUEST_END_ITEM_NAME$ from the Hellhounds to us for forging.

English: Very well… but the Hellhounds still lurk around Kaillun.
Spanish: Very well… but the Hellhounds still lurk around Kaillun.

English: You don’t have enough. Their fangs are essential to forge weapons that can repel them.
Spanish: You don’t have enough. Their fangs are essential to forge weapons that can repel them.

English: Excellent work! Thanks to you, we can forge weapons worthy of the finest Muran warriors.
Spanish: Excellent work! Thanks to you, we can forge weapons worthy of the finest Muran warriors.

English: $QUEST_END_NPC_NAME$ thanks you from the bottom of his heart! Glory to the Murans!
Spanish: $QUEST_END_NPC_NAME$ thanks you from the bottom of his heart! Glory to the Murans!
